🚨 The issue tracker is not for questions 🚨

i'm trying to implement vscode extension which is language client (written in typescript) that communicates with LSP server which is written in OCaml. for that, i need to debug my extension step by step using breakpoints i read the documentation but it doesn't work : 

https://code.visualstudio.com/api/language-extensions/language-server-extension-guide#Debugging-both-client-and-server

here is launch.json:
{
	"version": "0.2.0",
	"configurations": [
		{
			"type": "node",
			"request": "launch",
			"name": "Launch Client",
			"runtimeExecutable": "${execPath}",
			"args": ["--extensionDevelopmentPath=${workspaceRoot}"],
			"preLaunchTask": {
				"type": "npm",
				"script": "watch"
			}
		},
		{
			"type": "ocaml",
			"request": "attach",
			"name": "Attach to Server",
			"port": 6009,
			"restart": true,
		}
	],
	"compounds": [
		{
			"name": "Client + Server",
			"configurations": ["Launch Client", "Attach to Server"]
		}
	]
}
